traceability.evidence:
In src/build-rows.js the implementation only computes the age for the single ‘latest’ version:

  const versionTimes = await fetchVersionTimes(name);
  const latestTime = versionTimes[info.latest];
  if (latestTime) {
    age = calculateAgeInDays(latestTime);
  }

There is no iteration over all versions newer than the current, nor any filtering to fetch only those versions. No tests cover fetching or displaying ages for multiple versions or the “smart fetching” optimization. The acceptance criteria (“fetch all versions and their publish dates”, “calculate age for each version”, “display ages alongside each version”, “only fetch newer versions”) are not met by this code.
